            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Behold, if the Lord . . . this thing be?—This may be correct. Even granting the very unlikely supposition that Jehovah is about to make windows (Genesis 7:11) in the sky, to rain down supplies through them, the promised cheapness of provisions can hardly ensue so soon. Or we may render, “Behold, Jehovah is going to make windows in the sky [i.e., to pour down provisions upon us]. Can this thing come to pass?” In any case, the tone is that of scoffing unbelief. Reuss renders, with French point, “Voyez donc. Iaheweh en fera pleuvoir! Est ce que c’est chose possible?”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Behold, if the Lord . . . this thing be?—This may be correct. Even granting the very unlikely supposition that Jehovah is about to make windows (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 7:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") in the sky, to rain down supplies through them, the promised cheapness of provisions can hardly ensue so soon. Or we may render, “Behold, Jehovah is going to make windows in the sky [",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "i.e.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", to pour down provisions upon us]. Can this thing come to pass?” In any case, the tone is that of scoffing unbelief. Reuss renders, with French point, “Voyez donc. Iaheweh en fera pleuvoir! Est ce que c’est chose possible?”",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Behold, thou shalt see.—Literally, Behold, thou art about (i.e., destined) to see. Elisha partly imitates the speech of the scoffer, which begins in the Hebrew with “Behold, Jehovah is about to make windows.” (Comp. 2Kings 5:26.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Behold, thou shalt see.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Behold, thou art about ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(",
