  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Then a lord, on whose hand the king leaned,.... Not figuratively, in whom the king confided, but literally, on whose hand he rested, and by whom he was supported, being a form and matter of state, while he and Elisha were talking together, or on whom he leaned as he came to him; this was a principal lord, the third to the king, as his title seems to denote; the word by which the Septuagint renders it is by Suidas (u) interpreted of such that held three spears in the hand together; and this was an honourable post, for a king to lean on him; such state was used by the king of Syria, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 5:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and by the kings and queens of Persia; so Gorionides (w) says of Esther, that on the third day; she put on her beautiful garments and glorious ornaments, and took two of her maidens with her, and put her right hand on one of them, and leaned upon her in a royal manner, or as was the manner of kings: the same ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "answered the man of God; the prophet of the Lord, as the Targum: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and said, behold, if the Lord would make windows in heaven, might this thing be? it is impossible it should be, if he was to open the windows of heaven as at the flood, and let down showers of wheat and barley, in like manner as he rained manna in the wilderness: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and he said; the prophet in reply to him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "behold, thou shalt see it with thine eyes, but shalt not eat thereof; wheat and barley sold at the above price, but should not taste of it, as a punishment of his unbelief. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(u) In voce  (w) Heb. Hist. l. 2. c. 4. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(u) In voce  (w) Heb. Hist. l. 2. c. 4. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
