            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Behold,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " if ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Lord would",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [R.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "should",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "make windows in heaven",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] There is no mark of the hypothesis in the Hebrew, as is shewn by the italic ‘if’ of A.V. But the sense is hypothetical. Literally the words are ‘Behold the Lord [is] making &c.’ This is said in derision. Almost as if the captain had said, ‘I suppose then the Lord is going to make &c.’ and then he follows his scorn with a question. ‘Even then, could [R.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "might",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] this thing be?’ For ‘windows of heaven’ cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 7:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "thou shalt see",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " it ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "with thine eyes",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The answer to this mocking captain would be as hard for him to comprehend as was the promise of abundance which he was deriding. He, a person in close attendance on the king, to see the store which was promised and not partake of it was inconceivable. Doubtless his mockery grew louder still.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
